//DOCUMENT DESCRIPTION
                                        //WEB LAYOUT using HTML5 & CSS3//


1> WRAP :   * It used to group together related elements for semantic purposes/styling.
            * margin:auto; //center aligned all div/page/section/content    

2> WEB LAYOUT ELEMENTS :

    * HEADER : header for a document
         
    * NAVIGATION :  set of navigation links

    * CONTENT (like sidebar)
        * SECTION : section in a document
        * ARTICLE : self-contained content

    * ASIDE : Defines content aside from the content (like sidebar)

    * FOOTER : footer for a document

3> In Parent section->
    --> for parent - use clearfix property

        --> clearfix
           * To bring the height back
             we need to use clearfix class in main-div(parent)

           * we should have to clear both float affect on the parent-
             use clear: both

           * (.clearfix::after) -> used pseudo class:
                    used to add styles to selectors,
                    but, only when those selectors meet certain conditions.
                    A pseudo class is expressed by adding a colon (:)
                    eg-"hover", "focus", "active"

    --> inspect-> settings-> more tools -> developers tool ->elements 
                        main-div(parent) height will check. 
                         (& to bring the height the back in Parent )

       
4> Child section -->
         -> for child use "float" property
         -> we need to remove hight from main-div(parent) so, child can float both left and right side 
         -> when the elements float, there is no content in the parent : then height will be "0"
                   (-> to bring the height the back , we need to use clearfix class in parent )